Surgical Care Affiliates (SCA) is a company established in 2007 that maintains a nationwide network of hospitals and ambulatory care centers. This organization operates 145 ambulatory centers and surgical hospitals across the country.

UnitedHealth is in the process of purchasing SCA.… MoreSurgical Care Affiliates (SCA) is a company established in 2007 that maintains a nationwide network of hospitals and ambulatory care centers. This organization operates 145 ambulatory centers and surgical hospitals across the country.

UnitedHealth is in the process of purchasing SCA.  The deal is slated to close in mid-2017.
IT Priorities:
• In June, 2013, Surgical Care Affilicates (SCA) acquired Health Inventures. Information Technology resources are currently being integrated.
• SCA is using Windows technologies to develop its cloud environment. Additional cloud solutions, such as Office 360 are being considered.

IT Vendors:
•… MoreIT Priorities:
• In June, 2013, Surgical Care Affilicates (SCA) acquired Health Inventures. Information Technology resources are currently being integrated.
• SCA is using Windows technologies to develop its cloud environment. Additional cloud solutions, such as Office 360 are being considered.

IT Vendors:
• The company relies primarily on a combination of SAP and Microsoft-based enterprise resource planning (ERP) solutions.
• SCA hospitals use Epic electronic medical records (EMR), as well as Echo electronic health records (EHR).
• The financial environment utilizes Peoplesoft 9.0.

IT Intelligence Snippets
• A formal Bring Your Own Device (BYOD) policy is in place, with mobile device management (MDM) and security solutions enabling use of personal smart phone and tablet devices. However, no personal laptops or personal computers are authorized at this time.
• The company has implemented ECOSystem across all facilities.
• The company currently has no need for big data or data management solutions.





